<figureCitation box="[159,252,261,287]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1799,1824]" captionTargetBox="[166,1422,181,1763]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[151,1435,166,1779]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 2. Selected Portuguese species. A. Acropsilus niger (♂); B. Anahydrophorus cinereus (♂); C. Anepsiomyia flaviventris (♂); D. A. flaviventris (♀); E. Aphrosylus celtiber (♂); F. Aphrosylus ferox (♂); G. Argyra leucocephala (♂); H. A. leucocephala (♀); I. Campsicnemus curvipes (♂); J. Campsicnemus loripes (♂); K. Campsicnemus simplicissimus (♂); L. Campsicnemus umbripennis (♂); M. Ceratopos seguyi (♂); N. C. seguyi (♀); O. Chrysotimus molliculus (copula); photos by Rui Andrade, except for M by Valter Jacinto." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3357627/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Figs 2A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[264,276,261,287]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="55.[151,250,1172,1197]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,179,1141]" captionTargetId="figure@55.[151,1435,166,1153]" captionTargetPageId="55" captionText="FIGURE 8. Selected Portuguese habitats of dolichopodid species. A. 4 km SSW of Manteigas, Serra da Estrela, river Zêzere, May 2014 (Orthoceratium sabulosum); B. Mouriscas, Tejo river, March 2011 (Medetera feminina); C. Salreu, Ria de Aveiro, June 2010 (Dolichopus andalusiacus, Chrysotus gramineus); D. Santa Luzia, April 2011 (Medetera ambigua); E. Santa Margarida da Coutada, March 2011 (Syntormon pallipes); F. São Marcos da Serra, Ribeira de Odelouca, September 2010 (Acropsilus niger, Hercostomus verbekei, Sybistroma dufourii); G. detail of same location; H. Tornada, Paul de Tornada, July 2010 (Poecilobothrus bigoti, Poecilobothrus principalis); I. detail of same location, with yellow pan trap." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3357639/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">8</figureCitation>
F–G)
