<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="24" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1436,333,612]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,369,396]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Distribution.</emphasis>
Northwestern and central Europe; also North Africa. 
<collectingCountry box="[960,1059,369,395]" name="Portugal" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Portugal</collectingCountry>
: four provinces, both in the north and the south (this study), and Beira Alta (
<bibRefCitation author="Naglis, S. &amp; Bartak, M." box="[625,878,405,432]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" pagination="125 - 137" refId="ref33294" refString="Naglis, S. &amp; Bartak, M. (2015) Dolichopodidae (Diptera) from the Iberian Peninsula, with description of three new species. Zootaxa, 3964 (1), 125 - 137. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3964.1.9" type="journal article" year="2015">Naglis &amp; Barták 2015</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="24" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1436,333,612]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,300,442,468]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Ecology.</emphasis>
Largely confined to river banks, both in Mediterranean (Algarve) and in mountainous areas (northern 
<collectingCountry box="[151,248,477,504]" name="Portugal" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Portugal</collectingCountry>
) between 
<quantity box="[362,419,477,504]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" unit="m" value="80.0">80 m</quantity>
and 
<specimenCount box="[473,551,477,504]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" type="generic">
<quantity box="[473,546,477,504]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" unit="m" value="750.0">750 m</quantity>
.
</specimenCount>
In 
<collectingCountry box="[587,686,477,503]" name="Belgium" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Belgium</collectingCountry>
, it has been found on both sandy banks of lakes and gravelly banks of large rivers.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1436,333,612]" box="[199,763,549,576]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,549,576]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Rarity (%).</emphasis>
5.7 (fairly rare). Extremely rare (FL).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1436,333,612]" box="[199,648,585,612]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,386,585,612]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Activity period.</emphasis>
June, August–October.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
